<br>
I suspect rogues are actually more common (percentage wise) on the neutral team than the evil team.  I'm in the most powerful neutral guild, and rogue seems to be pretty close to our most common class.  So in answer to your question I'd say that a non-evil rogue has a very good chance of &quot;making it&quot; on the server on a team other than evil...if that team is neutral at least.  I don't know much about playing good though.  <br>
<br>
In general one thing that is cool about Sullon Zek is that most players here had the high-level game in mind from the beginning, so class balence is really good as compared to other PvP servers where everyone is playing necros and druids.  Also most people here (at least on the neutral team) seem to be much more experienced in the high level game then they were on TZ which is the only other server I've played on.<br>
