that don't correspond much to the in-game action.  Just like most<br>
of the web, there is 5% or so of useful information.<br>
<br>
The best part of that board is the Trade board, its the<br>
place to spend time on.<br>
<br>
When in game, PvP is usually silent, fast, deadly.<br>
There is only talk once the encounter is over. Often<br>
congratulatory, sometimes not, but whatever is said<br>
reflects on the person saying it.  Take the posturing<br>
as part of the game. (Just like many sports) And it's mostly<br>
hot air.<br>
<br>
The thing to do is get into a guild quickly. Get lots of<br>
information on the lay of the land. Alot can be learned from<br>
/guildsay.  You need to pool resources in a guild setup.<br>
Find a mid-level guild that is mature, likes to PvP, or<br>
PvE, whatever you like to do most. <br>
<br>
Because of the 1 char/account alot of SZ is lvl 30-60,<br>
so it is alot easier to be lower level now than it was<br>
at the beginning of SZ. <br>
<br>
Level up, once at a higher level, perhaps you might be able<br>
to get into the lvl 50+ guilds.  <br>
But I would caution to enjoy the lower levels though.<br>
Some people level to 35-40 then stop and just PvP,<br>
those are the ideal levels imho.<br>
<br>
Once lvl 50+, player capabilities are so high that PvP<br>
is more group oriented and the solo PvP is tougher because<br>
of resists and other factors.<br>
<br>
(Unless you are a manaburning/lifeburning wizard/necro. =)<br>
BTW, I would suggest that both those skills need longer cast times<br>
and Line of Sight restrictions.  Perhaps even restricted to<br>
NPCs only. )<br>
